 <p><b>VISITING PROFESSOR OR RESEARCH SCHOLAR AGREEMENT</b></p>
 <p><b>Universidad de La Salle</b></p>
 <p><b>And</b></p>
 <p><b>INGENIERÍA INFORMÁTICA INTEGRAL LTDA - INFOTEGRA</b></p>
 <p><b>Date: [mm/dd/yyyy]</b></p>
 </div>
 <p>Universidad de La Salle (UdLS) extends an invitation to [Name of Professor or Researcher], from the [name of the school] at the INGENIERÍA INFORMÁTICA INTEGRAL LTDA - INFOTEGRA as a visiting professor or research scholar from [mm/dd/yyyy].</p>
 <p><b>I.	Objectives of the collaboration:</b></p>
 <ul>
 <li>This cooperation will benefit both institutions at teaching and research levels. Both institutions have a multidisciplinary interest in the general topic of [name of the general topic]. In this context, both institutions have an interest in applied [specific activities to perform or subjects to considerate] and, through this cooperation, will work to strengthen that agenda in the teaching and research taking place in both places. This cooperation will focus specifically in the areas of [name of the specific areas].</li>
 <li>Establish articulation agreements in areas of [name of the specific areas].</li>
 <li>Assist in the formulation and establishment of elements and modules for [specific activities to perform or subjects to considerate]</li>
 <li>Discuss a long term cooperation to explore a programme in the area [name of the specific areas].</li>
 <li>Discuss the perspectives of applied topics and user experience in the field of [name of the specific areas], both from the teaching and research collaboration levels.</li>
 <li>Assist in the formulation in the area of [name of the specific areas] research.</li>
 <li>Assist in the development of research specific activities to perform or subjects to considerate].</li>
 <li>Give academic lectures or classes to students at the .</li>
 </ul>
 <p><b>II.	Specific responsibilities of the visiting professor or research scholar:</b></p>
 <ul>
 <li>The visiting professor or research scholar must apply for a visa at the Colombian Embassy in his/her country of origin. (According to the case)</li>
 <li>According to Colombian regulations, all visiting professors or research scholars are to show an invitation letter that will be necessary to enter the country with his/her air ticket to return. In order to comply with such requirement, the Colombian Government has established migration procedures under new Decree 0834 Art. 21, PIP-6 in which a Temporary Permission is given.</li>
 <li>The visiting scholar should ask for a Colombian ID whether his/her stay is more than three (3) months. He/ She must ask for this official document within the next fifteen (15) days upon his/her arrival.</li>
 <li>The visiting professor or research scholar must give copy of his/her Colombian visa, copy of his/her passport, copy of his/her insurance policy, copy of his/her curriculum vitae, copy of his/her flight itinerary, copy of the Colombian ID (if applies) to the International Affairs Office.</li>
 <li>The visiting professor or research scholar must purchase by his/her own means an international insurance policy. This insurance will cover the dates of the visit, and will be required to comprise: a) Accidental death -including transportation and repatriation of the remains-; b) Total and permanent disability; c) Medical Expenses; and d) Dental Expenses. </li>
 <li>The visiting professor or research scholar must specify the teaching methodology, his/her presentations and his/her lecturer obligations in the  at Universidad de La Salle.</li>
 <li>The visiting professor will actively work with the staff of Universidad de la Salle to promote student exchange, articulation agreements, research collaboration and possible joint degrees.</li>
 </ul>
 <p><b>III.	Support provided by Universidad de La Salle (UdLS):</b></p>
 <ul>
 <li>UdLS designates the person named in the agreement as an International Visiting Professor or Research Scholar at the  for the time specified in the agreement and he/she must be officially notified to the International Affairs Office at UdLS by the corresponding Dean.</li>
 <li>The Dean of the  must notify the International Affairs Office at UdLS the benefits and details that the visiting professor or research scholar will receive during his/her visit.</li>
 <li>The Dean of the  at UdLS will provide assistance about functions, academic tasks and responsibilities designated to the visiting professor or research scholar during his/her visit. In this case the Dean may designate the Director of an Academic Program to follow up with the activities designated to the International Visiting Professor or Research Scholar.</li>
 </ul>
 <p><b>IV.	UdLS -  and the INGENIERÍA INFORMÁTICA INTEGRAL LTDA - INFOTEGRA represented by [Name of Professor or Research Scholar at foreign institution] agree that:</b></p>
 <ul>
 <li>UdLS through the  will identify and assign a faculty member who will collaborate with the visiting professor or research scholar during his/her visit.</li>
 <li>UdLS will grant [amount to be paid] for a maximum of 40 hours that will be provided from the ; this grant will cover living expenses and as a travel allowance. If there are fewer hours scheduled the same grant will be provided. A tax deduction of 7% is compulsory according to legal regulations.</li>
 <li>The  at UdLS will provide assistance according to the official process with the Colombian authorities and the migration status in Colombia during the length of his/her academic or research activity.</li>
 <li>UdLS will provide accommodation within its campus during the length of his/her academic or research activity and any other arrangements officially notified by UdLS. The visiting professor or research scholar may cease this service; in such case, UdLS may help find an appropriate space but will not assume the costs of accommodation or of any prejudice or situation that may occur.</li>
 <li>[It is necessary to choose one of the following options]:</li>
 <li>UdLS will provide round trip tickets to the visiting professor or research scholar. ICETEX may participate as sponsor under the special program for visiting scholars, in such case; UdLS will have to comply with the requirements established by the above mentioned institution.</li>
 <li>UdLS will provide round trip, economy class tickets to the visiting scholar. In case air tickets have been purchased by UdLS and there’s cancellation under any circumstance by the visiting scholar, a full reimbursement will be done in the next 30 days after such notification.</li>
 <li>The visiting professor or research scholar must be in charge of any other not agreed costs.</li>
 <li>The ; will specify physical facilities available to the professor or research scholar including office space, laboratory space (if applies) or any other facilities.</li>
 <li>The ; will specify support resources available to the professor or research scholar as computer, internet and office equipment if it is necessary.</li>
 <li>The ; will specify if access to the library, information networks will be available to the professor or research scholar (if applies and if it is necessary).</li>
 <li>The visiting professor or research scholar is responsible of the physical facilities he/she uses and in case of any damage, he/she or its institution is in charge of paying the corresponding repairs.</li>
 <li>The ; will specify the language of instruction if different to Spanish.</li>
 </ul>
 <p>This agreement is valid for the time above mentioned. The signatures below verify approval and consent of the visiting professor or research scholar as specified in this agreement.</p>
